20 July 2015Deputy Minister of Communications, Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams will do her 67-minute bit on the 21st July 2015, Kwalindile Village in Mthatha, Eastern CapeThe Deputy Minister of Communications, Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams in partnership with Vodacom and Eastern Cape AIDS Council will first interact with the community, handover blankets to the elderly and needy, and handover schoolbags and water-bottles. Furthermore, donate schools shoes for both boys and girls, sanitary towels for the schoolgirls, mobile cyber lab with tablets, laptop, projector, white board and a printer. During the interactions with the community, the Deputy Minister and her entourage will also participate in the planting of seedlings in few selected households.Members of the media are invited as follows: Date: Tuesday, 21st July 2015 Time: 10:00 Venue: Kwalindile Village, Mthatha, Eastern CapeRSVP: Vuyani Sibene 073 092 9589 vuyani@gcis.gov.za Enquiries: Mzimasi Ngqelu 0769043557 mzi@doc.gov.za Issued by Government Communications (GCIS) on behalf of Ministry of Communications